Thanks <a href="https://www.codeplex.com/site/users/view/GOstrowsky" rel="nofollow">GOstrowsky</a> You saved my life :) :) <br />
<br />
I've just downloaded your code, and it works perfectly, however, it adds a view one time, for the second it raises the following exception: <br />
<br />
<img src="https://wtiuka.blu.livefilestore.com/y2pZ5hKbPGcyHGZOgvYAgp8FOzQCnvfNexW6D0c2I4Z4OBdU3mlBVYIrVOrZUXVylB9O5jJ584zc7rbkMvoS0FSfrC0vA95rqU5WJRjSgWkaks/exception_modview.png?psid=1" alt="Exception" /><br />
<br />
I solved the problem by adding a new static variable to avoid getting the same views names in the the region manager as the following: <br />
<div style="color:Black;background-color:White;"><pre>
<span style="color:Blue;">private</span> <span style="color:Blue;">static</span> <span style="color:Blue;">int</span> viewCounter;

        <span style="color:Blue;">public</span> HelloWorldViewModel()
        {
            AddView = <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> DelegateCommand
                (
                () =&gt;
                    {
                        viewCounter++;
                        ServiceLocator.Current.GetInstance&lt;IRegionManager&gt;().Regions[<span style="color:#A31515;">&quot;RegionInsideDataTemplate&quot;</span>].Add(
                            <span style="color:Blue;">string</span>.Format(<span style="color:#A31515;">&quot;View {0} added through View Injection&quot;</span>, viewCounter));
                    }
                );

            MyRegionManager = ServiceLocator.Current.GetInstance&lt;IRegionManager&gt;();
            RaisePropertyChanged(<span style="color:#A31515;">&quot;MyRegionManager&quot;</span>);
        }
</pre></div>Thanks a lot :) <br />
